#: ''the '''gripe''' of a sword''
# {{lb|en|engineering|dated}} A device for grasping or holding anything; a [[brake]] to stop a [[wheel]].
# Oppression; cruel exaction; affiction; pinching distress.
#: ''the gripe of poverty''
# {{lb|en|chiefly|in the plural}} Pinching and spasmodic pain in the intestines.
# {{lb|en|nautical}} The piece of [[timber]] that terminates the [[keel]] at the [[fore]] end; the [[forefoot]].
# {{lb|en|nautical}} The [[compass]] or sharpness of a ship's [[stern]] under the water, having a tendency to make her keep a good wind.
# {{lb|en|nautical}} An assemblage of ropes, dead-eyes, and hocks, fastened to ringbolts in the deck, to secure the boats when hoisted.
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[vulture]], ''Gyps fulvus''; the [[griffin]].
#* Shakespeare
#*: Like a white hind under the '''gripe's''' sharp claws.

